title: For Sale:  1903 A3 Springfield 30-06
postcontent:
This is a great gun.  She stacks rounds very well at 100 yards.  She loves to shoot Remington Core-Lokt in 180 gr. ($18 per box at Bi-Mart limit 5 boxes per person)

The bluing on this gun is better than I have seen on any other 1903 Springfield.  The bolt is polished. New Timney trigger, set well out of the box but its adjustable.  I will provide the original trigger as well.  The safety works great.  The empty round/bolt release works perfect.  Free floating barrel on a new laminated sporterized stock from Boyd's.  Rifle sling and NEW matte finish, Burris long eye relief, 4.5x14x42mm scope. Ballistic Plex reticle.

I love this gun and there is only one reason I am selling it.  I am a Sako fan and there is a Sako .300 win mag that has become available.  I have had my eye on the Sako for over 8 years and now I can get it.  I am selling a few items in order to obtain it. Im also selling a Smith and Wesson 9mm

If you don't want the scope on this rifle I will keep it and you can take 300 off the price. It will go nice on the Sako.   I am firm on my price, and I will not trade.

The rifle comes with the boxes of shells you see in the pictures.  The Core-Lokt are the ones to shoot in the rifle.  She may like other brands of heavier bullets but she doesn't like the 150 gr in these Federal or the Remington Sonics.  I think a 1" group at 100yards is damn good for a 100 year old gun.  You cant find good steel like this anymore.

Ryan
REDACTED
